'''Teymanak-e Olya''' ({{lang-fa|تيمنك عليا}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Teymanak-e ‘Olyā''' and '''Teymanak ‘Olyā'''; also known as '''Teymanak''' and '''Teymanak-e Bālā''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3087388|Teymanak-e Olya}}</ref> is a village in [[Jolgeh-ye Musaabad Rural District]], in the [[Central District (Torbat-e Jam County)|Central District]] of [[Torbat-e Jam County]], [[Razavi Khorasan Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 559, in 117 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|09}}</ref>
